panels.description: The OverOps dashboard (e.g. app.overops.com) provides **developers** a detailed analysis of errors within the target application(s) and direct links to **Root cause**.
panels.title: OverOps Classic

panels.description: The Reliability Analysis  dashboard provides **developers** with a list of all new errors, increasing errors and slowdowns for a target app or deployment and direct links to their **Root Cause**.
panels.title: RC Analysis

panels.description: The Reliability Scorecard dashboard provides **QA and Dev managers** a summary of **Reliability scores** for the applications, deployment and code tiers.
panels.title: QA Scorecard

panels.description: The Site Reliability enables **DevOps and SREs** to observe the **functionality and performance** of key transactions and failure rate for target application(s) in real-time.
panels.title: Site Reliability

panels.description: The Performance dashboard enables **SREs and DevOps** to observe the **performance of transactions** for target applications(s) including deviations in response tines and failure rates.
panels.title: Performance

panels.description: The Event Diff dashboard enables **QA and Devs** to compare any set of applications and deployments to one another to see which errors have been introduced or increased **release over release** or between different time periods (e.g. today vs. last week).
panels.title: Compare

panels.description: The Reliability Review dashboard enables software **execs and managers** to observe how **applications trend** across different reliability KPIs such as score, new errors, volume over time, and compare between different applications.
panels.title: Trend

panels.description: The Settings console enables **OverOps admins** to manage environment, integrations and permissions as well as customize the behaviour of the different Reliability dashboards.
panels.title: Settings

panels.description: A report providing a weighted score of the key applications, as defined in the Settings dashboard. Key applications are marked with * and appear at the top of the list followed by applications with the highest event volume up to limit of  $limit applications in total. Score weights are defined in the Settings dashboard.
